arStrings.szText: Yes. You did well, the demon is truly banished. I'm impressed you were able to copy the ritual so quickly. It took me ages to master.
Groggy, weak, waking up from a horrible nightmare.
Sister Octavia, you are all right! But these people have engaged in blasphemy of the highest sort! Lying! Stealing holy implements! Brutalizing a priest of the Cathedral!
They will burn on the pyre before the day is out! How could you be so rash? When the Reverend Mother--
Oh? And what will you tell Prava? That you allowed a commoner to so easily deceive her holy representative? That you abandoned your flock in Margrave and left them with no guidance from the Light?
smug but cold. This is a threat.
If I am to be tied to that horrific pyre, then you shall be there with me!
cold, direct. This is a threat.
I suppose I have been away from Margrave overlong. I should return swiftly.
backpedalling from a threat. Trying to escape and awkward conversation as quickly as possible.
But, Sister Octavia, please, take better care of yourself. The Cathedral is stronger with you on your feet than in a sick bed.
earnest. Octavia is important to you. more warmly than you would normally speak to someone.
